article.headline: Arizona to face Washington
article.linkText: Arizona beats USC at the buzzer
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Lodrick Stewart scored 15 points and had five steals in Southern California's 90-52 victory over Occidental College on Friday. Rory O'Neil also scored 15 points for the Trojans. Errick Craven had 14 points and Gabriel Pruitt added 10. Southern Cal held Occidental to 28 percent shooting and led 52-19 at halftime. Ivan Kostic paced the Tigers with 22 points.
